mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>100</mn></msubsup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{x_i^n\\}_{n=1}^{100}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0728em;vertical-align:-0.2587em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4413em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2587em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4519em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">=</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">100</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2481em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>","key":"vl8kQDlbNY"},{"type":"text","value":", you can  evolve all of them in parallel until each generates a new effectively independent sample. This is roughly 100 times faster (in wallclock time) than collecting 100 samples from a single chain.","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"gswaMD2E3P"}],"key":"wE82yM2UMW"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The core idea of LAPS","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"NWcu1sLkwV"}],"identifier":"the-core-idea-of-laps","label":"The core idea of LAPS","html_id":"the-core-idea-of-laps","implicit":true,"key":"Ph3Y1qoznw"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It has been observed that among gradient-based MCMC methods, unadjusted kernels (i.e. kernels without Metropolis-Hastings) converge from the the typically poor initialization (cold start) to the vicinity of the target distribution (warm start) faster than adjusted ones. The idea of LAPS is simply to use the unadjusted kernel to get the warm start, and then switch to an adjusted kernel for fine convergence.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"GfhBsaoKtv"}],"key":"rBO2w0OhIC"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The details involve determining when this switching point should take place, and tuning the hyperparameters of the kernels.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"yNbXDFgHJP"}],"key":"prCqeYM7xy"}],"key":"AK251GbURD"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nplt.rcParams[\"axes.spines.right\"] = False\nplt.rcParams[\"axes.spines.top\"] = False\nplt.rcParams[\"font.size\"] = 19","visibility":"show","key":"ha2odYfNZa"},{"type":"outputs","id":"nTSF2TJHzx1WnhxsWLy2Z","children":[],"visibility":"show","key":"TvlDRhPIXw"}],"data":{"tags":[]},"visibility":"hide","key":"aSj3IjtvID"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"import jax\nimport jax.numpy as jnp\njax.config.update(\"jax_enable_x64\", True)\n\nnum_cores = jax.local_device_count()\nprint(num_cores)\n\nimport blackjax\nfrom blackjax.adaptation.laps import laps as run_laps\n\ndef laps(logdensity_fn, ndims,\n         sample_init, rng_key,\n         num_steps1, num_steps2,\n         num_chains, mesh):\n\n    info, grads_per_step, _acc_prob, final_state = run_laps(\n        logdensity_fn=logdensity_fn,\n        sample_init= sample_init,\n        ndims= ndims,\n        num_steps1=num_steps1,\n        num_steps2=num_steps2,\n        num_chains=num_chains,\n        mesh=mesh,\n        rng_key= rng_key,\n        early_stop= False,\n        diagonal_preconditioning= True,\n        steps_per_sample=15,\n        r_end=0.01,\n        diagnostics= False,\n        superchain_size= 1\n        )\n\n    return final_state.position","key":"yn0UoQzDJ9"},{"type":"outputs","id":"KCiAgZCqF6KNxS6LvyvX1","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":"1\n"},"key":"sxfD2A7VFG"}],"key":"Y01fGgyvHl"}],"key":"Tz7fuKzggx"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Example","position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"key":"BbuuVsA09O"}],"identifier":"example","label":"Example","html_id":"example","implicit":true,"key":"ylnQWuTb2O"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use LAPS as follows:","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"key":"tmkT5N7cSB"}],"key":"fp71ZQ9hLU"}],"key":"QPGu35hrNr"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ndims = 2\n\ndef logdensity_fn(x):\n    mu2 = 0.03 * (x[0] ** 2 - 100)\n    return -0.5 * (jnp.square(x[0] / 10.0) + jnp.square(x[1] - mu2))\n\n\nrng_key_sampling, rng_key_init = jax.random.split(jax.random.key(42))\n\n# Function that takes a random seed and produces a vector of parameters. Each chain will be initialized by calling this function with a different random seed.\nsample_init = lambda key: jax.random.normal(key, shape= ndims)","key":"xRgl7bai4a"},{"type":"outputs","id":"MA2bzfDWqtECY0ALkQpam","children":[],"key":"YGhOaGalZI"}],"key":"j5vEr6AQGa"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Run sampling:","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"key":"Fu3l7DNevy"}],"identifier":"run-sampling","label":"Run sampling:","html_id":"run-sampling","implicit":true,"key":"x076O4X2ka"}],"key":"RBolFbCyM4"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"num_chains = 256\nnum_steps1, num_steps2 = 100, 100\n\nmesh = jax.sharding.Mesh(jax.devices()[:1], 'chains')\n\nprint('Number of devices: ', len(jax.devices()))\n\ninfo, grads_per_step, _acc_prob, samples = run_laps(\n    logdensity_fn=logdensity_fn,\n    sample_init= sample_init,\n    ndims= ndims,\n    num_steps1=num_steps1,\n    num_steps2=num_steps2,\n    num_chains=num_chains,\n    mesh=mesh,\n    rng_key= jax.random.key(0),\n    early_stop= False,\n    diagonal_preconditioning= True,\n    steps_per_sample=15,\n    r_end=0.01,\n    diagnostics= False,\n    superchain_size= 1\n)","key":"r9jrkJhKoD"},{"type":"outputs","id":"XBoAImpC0UmOv4voR4hn9","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":"Number of devices:  1\n"},"key":"nPZNRXrjgj"}],"key":"VN1VuLIoVP"}],"key":"P52BwsxKE9"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Visualize the posterior samples:","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"key":"VmXN9r3hkv"}],"identifier":"visualize-the-posterior-samples","label":"Visualize the posterior samples:","html_id":"visualize-the-posterior-samples","implicit":true,"key":"wIcY8KinJz"}],"key":"lphGBVBSm4"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\n\nx1 = jnp.linspace(-35, 35, 500)\nx2 = jnp.linspace(-35, 35, 500)\nX1, X2= jnp.meshgrid(x1, x2)\nX = jnp.stack((X1, X2), axis=-1)\nZ = jnp.exp(jax.vmap(jax.vmap(logdensity_fn))(X))\n\nplt.plot(samples.position[:, 0], samples.position[:, 1], '.', color = 'teal')\nplt.contourf(X1, X2, Z, cmap = 'Greys')\nplt.axis('off')\nplt.show()","key":"zBrGe3pQUD"},{"type":"outputs","id":"wYUdIqWMNHa4XOCUO0kfZ","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"display_data","metadata":{},"data":{"text/plain":{"content":"<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>","content_type":"text/plain"},"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"f2cf7f1dc0185254d6a4ed73363de5a0","path":"/sampling-book/build/f2cf7f1dc0185254d6a4ed73363de5a0.png"}}},"key":"ImDTxT84NU"}],"key":"V4f7UouXdT"}],"key":"sNTgwkNOMK"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":144,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is the speed-up?","position":{"start":{"line":144,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"key":"RWcQsMuF4J"}],"identifier":"what-is-the-speed-up","label":"What is the speed-up?","html_id":"what-is-the-speed-up","implicit":true,"key":"pa1iToA3OV"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The above example runs 256 chains ","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"key":"ImrvY2RCW9"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"in parallel","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"key":"yfAtsesPvw"}],"key":"bPNSbNG1JQ"},{"type":"text","value":", each for 200 steps. So, apart from parallelism overhead, this should take about the same as running 1 chain for 200 steps.","position":{"start":{"line":146,"column":1},"end":{"line":146,"column":1}},"key":"FcmmNWM49O"}],"key":"zh6TPnRg3s"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":148,"column":1},"end":{"line":148,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To see how many independent samples we get, we can use the fact that we know (or rather, have an accurate estimate of) the true second moments of the 2D Banana, so we can report the difference between the true second moments and the estimate (we normalize by the second moment standard deviations):","position":{"start":{"line":148,"column":1},"end":{"line":148,"column":1}},"key":"d7mhd1vtGg"}],"key":"pwD1S7oM9w"}],"key":"sdUIlkb2my"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"python","executable":true,"value":"ground_truth_second_moment_mean=jnp.array([100.0, 19.0])\nground_truth_second_moment_standard_deviation=jnp.sqrt(jnp.array([20000.0, 4600.898]))\n\nestimated_second_moment_mean=jnp.mean(samples.position**2, axis=0)\n\nerror = (estimated_second_moment_mean - ground_truth_second_moment_mean) / ground_truth_second_moment_standard_deviation\n\nerror","key":"TBygQArpsS"},{"type":"outputs","id":"Z6SYfVq8eNbvAjhAKbCIV","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"execute_result","execution_count":6,"metadata":{},"data":{"text/plain":{"content":"Array([-0.13861278, -0.10832151], dtype=float64)","content_type":"text/plain"}}},"key":"rm5Ta6DeSn"}],"key":"YfIXCOeLr6"}],"key":"r0ukyYAB9l"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":162,"column":1},"end":{"line":162,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is the error one would obtain from 100 exact independent samples, so we can say that LAPS has given us an effective sample size of 100. To get the same from a sequential method would take a chain at least 10 times longer, so LAPS gives a wallclock speed-up here of at least an order of magnitude (and often quite a bit more - see the ","position":{"start":{"line":162,"column":1},"end":{"line":162,"column":1}},"key":"deZTxBB3CN"},{"type":"link","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.16696","position":{"start":{"line":162,"column":1},"end":{"line":162,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"paper","position":{"start":{"line":162,"column":1},"end":{"line":162,"column":1}},"key":"NqZ0Zw5SWB"}],"urlSource":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.16696","key":"UT8cviumwb"},{"type":"text","value":").","position":{"start":{"line":162,"column":1},"end":{"line":162,"column":1}},"key":"m2RxwCpy1L"}],"key":"HclvAVPDUz"}],"key":"f3suqQFCLG"}],"key":"G5acUKokw1"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"MEADS: Ensemble Adaptation for GHMC","url":"/algorithms/meads","group":"Algorithms"},"next":{"title":"Adjoint-Differentiated Laplace HMC","url":"/algorithms/laplace-hmc-demo","group":"Algorithms"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}